INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('79', '1', '2015-11-16 09:17:46', '2015-11-16 09:17:46', '', 'img7', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'img7', '', '', '2015-11-16 09:17:46', '2015-11-16 09:17:46', '', '0', 'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/img7.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('80', '1', '2015-11-17 03:29:35', '2015-11-17 03:29:35', '<header>By <a href=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/author/genthemesuser/\" rel=\"author\">keith davis</a></header>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/agentpress_pro_child_theme.jpg\" alt=\"agentpress pro genesis child theme review\" width=\"640\" height=\"520\" data-lazy-loaded=\"true\" />\r\n\r\nI’m not in the real estate business, but when I see a theme that looks as good as AgentPress Pro…. <em>I wish I was</em>.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"agentpress pro theme\" href=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/refer/agentpress-pro/\">AgentPress Pro</a> is the successor to the hugely popular AgentPress child theme from StudioPress, which set the standard for so long for real estate themes.\r\n\r\nThe new version has been brought up to date it looks gorgeous, is a dream to set up and integrates perfectly with the AgentPress Listings plugin.\r\n<blockquote>Rise above the market and achieve results by showcasing your professional services and up-to-the-minute resources with the buyer-friendly layouts of AgentPress. Your clients will thank you for it.\r\n<strong>StudioPress </strong></blockquote>\r\n<h3>AgentPress Pro comes packed with features</h3>\r\nAgentPress Pro is a modern WordPress real estate theme built on Genesis 2.0. It’s HTML5 enabled, fully Mobile responsive and is packed with features.\r\n<div><strong>Genesis 2.0 HTML5 ready child themes </strong>\r\nGenesis 2.0 was released in August 2013 and since then StudioPress have been updating old themes and producing new themes to be HTML5 ready.\r\nFor a full list of HTML5 ready child themes check out <a href=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/all-the-latest-genesis-child-themes/\">All the latest Genesis child themes</a>.</div>\r\nHere’s a quick rundown of the general features that you’ll find in AgentPress Pro:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Fully widgetised homepage</strong> – setting up the homepage and the rest of the theme is just a matter of dragging and dropping widgets into widget areas and adding your own content… none of that nasty coding required.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Four fabulous colour schemes</strong> – choose a colour scheme that matches your corporate image and colours. Choose from blue, green, gold and red. The demo site uses red.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Six layout options</strong> – choose from six layouts for all your listing, pages and posts including a full-width option.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Custom background and custom header</strong> – easily and quickly upload your own background and header images using the WordPress uploader.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Custom Menus</strong> – supports WordPress custom menus.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Featured Images</strong> – supports WordPress featured images.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Four Page Templates</strong> – comes with archives, blog, columns and landing page templates.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAll great features, but what about the features that make this theme a dedicated real estate theme? The features that make it easy to add and display listings and make it easy for your visitors to enter their own search criteria and find their dream property?\r\n<h3>Dedicated real estate features of AgentPress Pro</h3>\r\n<img src=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/agentpress_pro_search_bar.jpg\" alt=\"agentpress pro search bar\" width=\"640\" height=\"249\" data-lazy-loaded=\"true\" />\r\n\r\nA real estate theme only has to do two things, but it has to do them well – it has to:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Display your listings, in a visually pleasing and easy to access way.</li>\r\n	<li>Allow your visitors to search your listings based on their specific search criteria.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAgentPress Pro is configured to work perfectly with the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/agentpress-listings/\">AgentPress Listings plugin</a>… <em>and that’s where the magic begins</em>.\r\n\r\nOnce you install the AgentPress Listings plugin a new section called “Listings” appears in your toolbar on the LHS of your WordPress dashboard. Two Widgets also appear in your Widgets area: an AgentPress – Listing Search Widget and an AgentPress – Featured Listings Widget.\r\n<h5>Listings in your toolbar</h5>\r\nFrom the Listings menu you can add Taxonomies and Listing Terms and create Listings for each of your properties.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/agentpress_listings_plugin.jpg\" alt=\"agentpress pro listings plugin\" width=\"167\" height=\"295\" data-lazy-loaded=\"true\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Create Taxonomies</strong> – allows you to create / add your own search criteria for properties such as location, price, bedrooms etc.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Create Listing Terms</strong> – once you have your Listing Taxonomies set up, you can create the “Terms” associated with each Taxonomy. For instance under the Taxonomy of Bedrooms you could use the Terms two bedroom, three bedroom etc.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Create Property Listings</strong> – create Listings for each of your properties, assign a featured image and Taxonomies and Terms.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5>AgentPress – Listing Search Widget</h5>\r\nThe AgentPress – Listing Search Widget is used in the Home Featured widget area to create the Search bar. The Search bar uses the Taxonomies and Terms created using the Listings menu.\r\n<h5>AgentPress – Featured Listings widget</h5>\r\nThe AgentPress – Featured Listings widget is used in the Home Top widget area and on the demo site is configured to display 6 recent listings. These listings display in three columns and two rows.\r\n\r\nIf that all sounds a bit complicated then take a look at this short video by Genesis developer Carrie Dils, which shows you how easy it is to use the AgentPress Listings plugin to set up the “search bar” area.\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/QiZAZQtxFk8?rel=0\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n<h3>Setting up AgentPress Pro</h3>\r\nYou might think that a theme that has the functionality of <a title=\"agentpress pro theme\" href=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/refer/agentpress-pro/\">AgentPress Pro</a> is difficult to set up. Fortunately the Genesis developers have done all the hard work… so that we don’t have to.\r\n\r\nThe whole theme is set up using plugins and widget areas. All you have to do is drag and drop a few widgets, do a little typing and hit save.\r\n\r\nTo replicate the demo site you need to install four plugins:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/agentpress-listings/\">AgentPress Listings</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/simple-social-icons/\">Simple Social Icons</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/genesis-enews-extended/\">Genesis – eNews Extended Widget</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/jquery-lightbox-for-native-galleries/\">jQuery Lightbox for Native Galleries</a>\r\n<div><strong>Full setup instructions in the StudioPress download area </strong>\r\nWhen you purchase a StudioPress child theme, you’ll be given access to the StudioPress download area.\r\nThis area contains all the themes you’ve purchased plus comprehensive setup instructions for each theme including screenshots and any HTML code used in the demo site.\r\nThe setup instructions also give details of plugins and plugin settings used on the demo site.</div>\r\nThe StudioPress setup documentation for AgentPress Pro gives full details on how each area is configured to match the demo site and the documentation is broken down into the following sections:\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>AgentPress Pro setup documentation sections</h3>\r\n<div><strong>First Steps</strong>\r\nPre-Installation Setup\r\nChild Theme Installation<strong>Genesis Theme Settings</strong>\r\nGenesis Theme Settings\r\nSite Title Header Text\r\nCustom Header Image\r\nHome Background Image\r\nNavigation Menus<strong>AgentPress Listings</strong>\r\nCreating Taxonomies\r\nCreating Listing Terms\r\nCreating a Property Listing\r\nHow To Import Demo Content\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div><strong>Home Page Setup</strong>\r\nHome Page Layout\r\nHome – Featured Widget Area\r\nHome – Top Widget Area\r\nHome – Middle Widget Areas\r\nHome – Bottom Widget Area<strong>Widget Areas</strong>\r\nPrimary Sidebar\r\nFooter Widget Areas\r\nDisclaimer Widget Area\r\nAfter Entry Widget Area<strong>Page Templates</strong>\r\nBlog Page Template\r\nArchive &amp; Landing Page Templates\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h6>Setting up the AgentPress Pro home page</h6>\r\nTo give you an idea of the quality of the setup instructions this is the information provided for setting up the home page, complete with fabulous graphic.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/agentpress_pro_homepage_setup.jpg\" alt=\"agentpress pro home page setup\" width=\"640\" height=\"1914\" data-lazy-loaded=\"true\" />\r\n\r\nThe home page is set up using nine widget areas, configured on the demo site as below:\r\n\r\n<strong>#1 Home Featured</strong> – a full-width widget area, which is set up with a text widget configured to display a Welcome message and an AgentPress – Listing Search Widget. The Home Page background image displays behind this widget area.\r\n\r\n<strong>#2 Home Top</strong> – a full-width widget area, set up with an AgentPress – Featured Listings widget configured to display 6 recent listings. These listings display in three columns and two rows.\r\n\r\n<strong>#3 Home Middle 1</strong> – a full-width widget area, set up with a text widget. This area is an ideal location to place a call-to-action on your home page.\r\n\r\n<strong>#4 Home Middle 2</strong> – a one-third width widget area, set up with a Genesis – eNews Extended widget.\r\n\r\n<strong>#5 Home Middle 3</strong> – a two-thirds width widget area, set up with a Genesis – Featured Posts widget configured to display 4 Posts with titles and Content limit of 213 Characters.\r\n\r\n<strong>#6 Home Bottom</strong> – a full-width widget area, set up with four featured page widgets configured to display the page title and a featured image.\r\n\r\n<strong>#7 Footer 1</strong> – a widget area, which displays in the left third of the footer area on all pages, including the Home Page. Any widget can be used in this area.\r\n\r\n<strong>#8 Footer 2</strong> – a widget area, which displays in the right two-thirds of the footer area on all pages, including the Home Page. Any widget can be used in this area.\r\n\r\n<strong>#9 Disclaimer</strong> – this Widget area displays beneath the footer credits area on all pages. This area can be used to display a legal disclaimer on your site.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note:</strong> If you don’t activate any of the home page widget areas, a blog-style home page will be displayed.\r\n<h3>Head over to StudioPress and pick up your copy of AgentPress Pro</h3>\r\nIf you’re a realtor using an old WordPress theme and looking for an upgrade or a real estate professional looking for a state-of-the-art theme to get started then AgentPress Pro is where you end your search.\r\n\r\nFor details of pricing head on over to StudioPress, <a title=\"agentpress pro theme\" href=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/refer/agentpress-pro/\">put AgentPress Pro through its paces</a> and pick up your copy today.\r\n<blockquote>AgentPress helps industry savvy real estate agents like you build a better business with its intuitive design, powerful functionality, and smart listings.\r\n<strong>StudioPress </strong></blockquote>\r\nHope you enjoyed the review and found it helpful and if you have any thoughts on WordPress real estate themes in general or AgentPress Pro in particular, I’d love to hear from you in the comments below.\r\nAnd if you’d like to spread the word about this fabulous theme please use my social sharing buttons.\r\n\r\n<strong>Credits:</strong>\r\nMy thanks and gratitude to <a title=\"studiopress\" href=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/refer/studiopress/\">StudioPress</a> for the graphics and details of the AgentPress Pro theme used in this post and special thanks to <a href=\"http://www.carriedils.com/\">Carrie Dils</a> for her fabulous AgentPress Listings video.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'AgentPress Pro Genesis child theme', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'agentpress-pro-genesis-child-theme', '', '', '2015-11-17 03:29:35', '2015-11-17 03:29:35', '', '0', 'http://localhost/?p=80', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('81', '1', '2015-11-17 03:28:10', '2015-11-17 03:28:10', '', 'agentpress_pro_child_theme', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'agentpress_pro_child_theme', '', '', '2015-11-17 03:28:10', '2015-11-17 03:28:10', '', '80', 'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/agentpress_pro_child_theme.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('82', '1', '2015-11-17 03:29:35', '2015-11-17 03:29:35', '<header>By <a href=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/author/genthemesuser/\" rel=\"author\">keith davis</a></header>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/agentpress_pro_child_theme.jpg\" alt=\"agentpress pro genesis child theme review\" width=\"640\" height=\"520\" data-lazy-loaded=\"true\" />\r\n\r\nI’m not in the real estate business, but when I see a theme that looks as good as AgentPress Pro…. <em>I wish I was</em>.\r\n\r\n<a title=\"agentpress pro theme\" href=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/refer/agentpress-pro/\">AgentPress Pro</a> is the successor to the hugely popular AgentPress child theme from StudioPress, which set the standard for so long for real estate themes.\r\n\r\nThe new version has been brought up to date it looks gorgeous, is a dream to set up and integrates perfectly with the AgentPress Listings plugin.\r\n<blockquote>Rise above the market and achieve results by showcasing your professional services and up-to-the-minute resources with the buyer-friendly layouts of AgentPress. Your clients will thank you for it.\r\n<strong>StudioPress </strong></blockquote>\r\n<h3>AgentPress Pro comes packed with features</h3>\r\nAgentPress Pro is a modern WordPress real estate theme built on Genesis 2.0. It’s HTML5 enabled, fully Mobile responsive and is packed with features.\r\n<div><strong>Genesis 2.0 HTML5 ready child themes </strong>\r\nGenesis 2.0 was released in August 2013 and since then StudioPress have been updating old themes and producing new themes to be HTML5 ready.\r\nFor a full list of HTML5 ready child themes check out <a href=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/all-the-latest-genesis-child-themes/\">All the latest Genesis child themes</a>.</div>\r\nHere’s a quick rundown of the general features that you’ll find in AgentPress Pro:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Fully widgetised homepage</strong> – setting up the homepage and the rest of the theme is just a matter of dragging and dropping widgets into widget areas and adding your own content… none of that nasty coding required.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Four fabulous colour schemes</strong> – choose a colour scheme that matches your corporate image and colours. Choose from blue, green, gold and red. The demo site uses red.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Six layout options</strong> – choose from six layouts for all your listing, pages and posts including a full-width option.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Custom background and custom header</strong> – easily and quickly upload your own background and header images using the WordPress uploader.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Custom Menus</strong> – supports WordPress custom menus.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Featured Images</strong> – supports WordPress featured images.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Four Page Templates</strong> – comes with archives, blog, columns and landing page templates.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAll great features, but what about the features that make this theme a dedicated real estate theme? The features that make it easy to add and display listings and make it easy for your visitors to enter their own search criteria and find their dream property?\r\n<h3>Dedicated real estate features of AgentPress Pro</h3>\r\n<img src=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/agentpress_pro_search_bar.jpg\" alt=\"agentpress pro search bar\" width=\"640\" height=\"249\" data-lazy-loaded=\"true\" />\r\n\r\nA real estate theme only has to do two things, but it has to do them well – it has to:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Display your listings, in a visually pleasing and easy to access way.</li>\r\n	<li>Allow your visitors to search your listings based on their specific search criteria.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAgentPress Pro is configured to work perfectly with the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/agentpress-listings/\">AgentPress Listings plugin</a>… <em>and that’s where the magic begins</em>.\r\n\r\nOnce you install the AgentPress Listings plugin a new section called “Listings” appears in your toolbar on the LHS of your WordPress dashboard. Two Widgets also appear in your Widgets area: an AgentPress – Listing Search Widget and an AgentPress – Featured Listings Widget.\r\n<h5>Listings in your toolbar</h5>\r\nFrom the Listings menu you can add Taxonomies and Listing Terms and create Listings for each of your properties.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/agentpress_listings_plugin.jpg\" alt=\"agentpress pro listings plugin\" width=\"167\" height=\"295\" data-lazy-loaded=\"true\" />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Create Taxonomies</strong> – allows you to create / add your own search criteria for properties such as location, price, bedrooms etc.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Create Listing Terms</strong> – once you have your Listing Taxonomies set up, you can create the “Terms” associated with each Taxonomy. For instance under the Taxonomy of Bedrooms you could use the Terms two bedroom, three bedroom etc.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Create Property Listings</strong> – create Listings for each of your properties, assign a featured image and Taxonomies and Terms.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5>AgentPress – Listing Search Widget</h5>\r\nThe AgentPress – Listing Search Widget is used in the Home Featured widget area to create the Search bar. The Search bar uses the Taxonomies and Terms created using the Listings menu.\r\n<h5>AgentPress – Featured Listings widget</h5>\r\nThe AgentPress – Featured Listings widget is used in the Home Top widget area and on the demo site is configured to display 6 recent listings. These listings display in three columns and two rows.\r\n\r\nIf that all sounds a bit complicated then take a look at this short video by Genesis developer Carrie Dils, which shows you how easy it is to use the AgentPress Listings plugin to set up the “search bar” area.\r\n<iframe src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/QiZAZQtxFk8?rel=0\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n<h3>Setting up AgentPress Pro</h3>\r\nYou might think that a theme that has the functionality of <a title=\"agentpress pro theme\" href=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/refer/agentpress-pro/\">AgentPress Pro</a> is difficult to set up. Fortunately the Genesis developers have done all the hard work… so that we don’t have to.\r\n\r\nThe whole theme is set up using plugins and widget areas. All you have to do is drag and drop a few widgets, do a little typing and hit save.\r\n\r\nTo replicate the demo site you need to install four plugins:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/agentpress-listings/\">AgentPress Listings</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/simple-social-icons/\">Simple Social Icons</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/genesis-enews-extended/\">Genesis – eNews Extended Widget</a>\r\n<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/jquery-lightbox-for-native-galleries/\">jQuery Lightbox for Native Galleries</a>\r\n<div><strong>Full setup instructions in the StudioPress download area </strong>\r\nWhen you purchase a StudioPress child theme, you’ll be given access to the StudioPress download area.\r\nThis area contains all the themes you’ve purchased plus comprehensive setup instructions for each theme including screenshots and any HTML code used in the demo site.\r\nThe setup instructions also give details of plugins and plugin settings used on the demo site.</div>\r\nThe StudioPress setup documentation for AgentPress Pro gives full details on how each area is configured to match the demo site and the documentation is broken down into the following sections:\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>AgentPress Pro setup documentation sections</h3>\r\n<div><strong>First Steps</strong>\r\nPre-Installation Setup\r\nChild Theme Installation<strong>Genesis Theme Settings</strong>\r\nGenesis Theme Settings\r\nSite Title Header Text\r\nCustom Header Image\r\nHome Background Image\r\nNavigation Menus<strong>AgentPress Listings</strong>\r\nCreating Taxonomies\r\nCreating Listing Terms\r\nCreating a Property Listing\r\nHow To Import Demo Content\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div><strong>Home Page Setup</strong>\r\nHome Page Layout\r\nHome – Featured Widget Area\r\nHome – Top Widget Area\r\nHome – Middle Widget Areas\r\nHome – Bottom Widget Area<strong>Widget Areas</strong>\r\nPrimary Sidebar\r\nFooter Widget Areas\r\nDisclaimer Widget Area\r\nAfter Entry Widget Area<strong>Page Templates</strong>\r\nBlog Page Template\r\nArchive &amp; Landing Page Templates\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h6>Setting up the AgentPress Pro home page</h6>\r\nTo give you an idea of the quality of the setup instructions this is the information provided for setting up the home page, complete with fabulous graphic.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/agentpress_pro_homepage_setup.jpg\" alt=\"agentpress pro home page setup\" width=\"640\" height=\"1914\" data-lazy-loaded=\"true\" />\r\n\r\nThe home page is set up using nine widget areas, configured on the demo site as below:\r\n\r\n<strong>#1 Home Featured</strong> – a full-width widget area, which is set up with a text widget configured to display a Welcome message and an AgentPress – Listing Search Widget. The Home Page background image displays behind this widget area.\r\n\r\n<strong>#2 Home Top</strong> – a full-width widget area, set up with an AgentPress – Featured Listings widget configured to display 6 recent listings. These listings display in three columns and two rows.\r\n\r\n<strong>#3 Home Middle 1</strong> – a full-width widget area, set up with a text widget. This area is an ideal location to place a call-to-action on your home page.\r\n\r\n<strong>#4 Home Middle 2</strong> – a one-third width widget area, set up with a Genesis – eNews Extended widget.\r\n\r\n<strong>#5 Home Middle 3</strong> – a two-thirds width widget area, set up with a Genesis – Featured Posts widget configured to display 4 Posts with titles and Content limit of 213 Characters.\r\n\r\n<strong>#6 Home Bottom</strong> – a full-width widget area, set up with four featured page widgets configured to display the page title and a featured image.\r\n\r\n<strong>#7 Footer 1</strong> – a widget area, which displays in the left third of the footer area on all pages, including the Home Page. Any widget can be used in this area.\r\n\r\n<strong>#8 Footer 2</strong> – a widget area, which displays in the right two-thirds of the footer area on all pages, including the Home Page. Any widget can be used in this area.\r\n\r\n<strong>#9 Disclaimer</strong> – this Widget area displays beneath the footer credits area on all pages. This area can be used to display a legal disclaimer on your site.\r\n\r\n<strong>Note:</strong> If you don’t activate any of the home page widget areas, a blog-style home page will be displayed.\r\n<h3>Head over to StudioPress and pick up your copy of AgentPress Pro</h3>\r\nIf you’re a realtor using an old WordPress theme and looking for an upgrade or a real estate professional looking for a state-of-the-art theme to get started then AgentPress Pro is where you end your search.\r\n\r\nFor details of pricing head on over to StudioPress, <a title=\"agentpress pro theme\" href=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/refer/agentpress-pro/\">put AgentPress Pro through its paces</a> and pick up your copy today.\r\n<blockquote>AgentPress helps industry savvy real estate agents like you build a better business with its intuitive design, powerful functionality, and smart listings.\r\n<strong>StudioPress </strong></blockquote>\r\nHope you enjoyed the review and found it helpful and if you have any thoughts on WordPress real estate themes in general or AgentPress Pro in particular, I’d love to hear from you in the comments below.\r\nAnd if you’d like to spread the word about this fabulous theme please use my social sharing buttons.\r\n\r\n<strong>Credits:</strong>\r\nMy thanks and gratitude to <a title=\"studiopress\" href=\"http://genesisthemes.co.uk/refer/studiopress/\">StudioPress</a> for the graphics and details of the AgentPress Pro theme used in this post and special thanks to <a href=\"http://www.carriedils.com/\">Carrie Dils</a> for her fabulous AgentPress Listings video.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'AgentPress Pro Genesis child theme', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '80-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-11-17 03:29:35', '2015-11-17 03:29:35', '', '80', 'http://localhost/index.php/2015/11/17/80-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('83', '1', '2015-11-17 14:05:09', '2015-11-17 14:05:09', 'At CoDA, we are enthusiastic followers of the Agile movement, proposing it as an alternative to traditional project management. Here we give you a short overview of Agile’s basics and two core concepts, user stories and <em>scrum</em> meetings, that revolutionized the way we think through and execute our projects.\r\n<h3>Agile project management basics <a class=\"sr hsl\" href=\"http://codifi.org/agile-project-management/?gclid=CjwKEAiAvauyBRDwuYf3qNyXmW4SJACX9-fXajOREFAZfj_OJ0cDqNdTd-xkl55RwHH7cVdDGJ-HHBoClVPw_wcB\" target=\"_blank\">link</a></h3>\r\nAgile was originally designed for software development, which is an integral part of our work. We use Agile both in developing and maintaining <a href=\"http://codifi.org/mukurtu\">Mukurtu.net tools and services</a> for web archiving and publishing of digital heritage, and in designing <a href=\"http://codifi.org/codifi/\">custom database solutions and data and media management workflows in our Codifi projects</a> with archaeologists around the world.\r\n\r\nBut over the years we – <a href=\"http://www.edenspiekermann.com/blog/agile-the-best-way-we-ever-worked\">and many others</a> – have tweaked the process to extend it to less traditional projects.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost/sharingMT//wp-content/uploads/2015/11/jvrp__jezreel_valley_regional_project_-_pivotal_tracker.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-178\" src=\"http://localhost/sharingMT//wp-content/uploads/2015/11/jvrp__jezreel_valley_regional_project_-_pivotal_tracker.png\" alt=\"jvrp__jezreel_valley_regional_project_-_pivotal_tracker\" width=\"2429\" height=\"1405\" /></a>\r\n\r\nIn brief, working with the agile methodology means:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Focussing on short iterations called ‘sprints’ of work, each delivering a working product increment;</li>\r\n	<li>Scheduling regular team check-ins (stand-ups or <em>scrum</em> meetings) to maximize the exchange of relevant information while saving everyone time;</li>\r\n	<li>Breaking project down into user-centric ‘stories’ that translate to tasks;</li>\r\n	<li>Keep tasks assigned, estimated in hours/days and prioritized into a product backlog.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agile_software_development\">Read more here</a> about the Agile methodology, originally designed for software development.\r\n\r\nProduct backlog can be a physical whiteboard; we find it convenient to use project management tools that offer ‘whiteboard metaphors’ such as Pivotal Tracker or Jira Agile. You will find plenty of these online, most offering either a trial limited in time or a free plan for small projects.\r\n<h3>User Stories, or what the project really is about</h3>\r\nUser Stories are a way to break down even the most complex project into communicable, measurable bits.\r\n\r\nUser stories are generally built with the following structure:\r\n\r\n<em>As a(n) “x” I want to be able to do “y” (so that “z”)</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>For a technical developer, this structure provides context as to why something is being implemented, as well as aid in prioritizing features.</li>\r\n	<li>For the client and non-technical stakeholders, having to break down the final product into detailed features helps immensely with designing the final user experience and thinking through all possible scenarios and audiences involved.</li>\r\n	<li>For everyone, stories quantify time and resources, while keeping the ‘why’ (goals) separated from the ‘how’ (specific tool or process), which allows creative solutions to emerge.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nA user story should also have detailed acceptance criteria that assist testing the story before approval.\r\n\r\nThis is an example of a user story we had in our backlog for the new <a href=\"http://codifi.org/mukurtu\">Mukurtu 2.0</a>, launching this month (March 2015).\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote><strong>As a Mukurtu site contributor I would like to add one or many cultural protocols to my Digital Heritage Item so that I can determine who has access to it.</strong>\r\n\r\nACCEPTANCE CRITERIA\r\n\r\nGiven that I am a Mukurtu site contributor, member of at least one community on the site, and I have identified the parameters under which I want my content to be shared, when I add a Digital Heritage item I would expect to be able to:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Only see the communities and protocols to which I have access</li>\r\n	<li>Share the content to</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>the community only</li>\r\n	<li>publicly and still have the community attribution</li>\r\n	<li>one or more communities and choose one or more protocols to fine-tune access</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Create content attributed to one or more communities and protocols to which I am AT LEAST a contributor AND can decide if the audience for my content must be members of all the assigned protocols, or either of the assigned protocols, pending approval</li>\r\n</ul></blockquote>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Execution: value everyone’s time</h3>\r\nScrum meetings provide a framework for keeping team-wide meetings short and concise (usually under 15 minutes depending on team size), while communicating effectively, tackling blockers and estimating progress. In interdisciplinary projects, frequent communication minimizes misunderstanding and settles responsibility and ownership issues that may arise over the course of the project.\r\n\r\nDuring daily (or regular) stand-ups, facilitated by a <em>Scrum Master</em>, each team member should quickly go through:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>work they’ve done since last meeting</li>\r\n	<li>what they’re working on until the next one, and</li>\r\n	<li>point out any blockers they’ve run into</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIndividual meetings to clear blockers, or further discussions on a specific issue, can follow or be scheduled now for a different time, so that no one has to sit through lengthy technical discussions that don’t involve them.\r\n\r\nAs <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scrum_%28software_development%29\">Wikipedia</a> puts it: “Any impediment/stumbling block identified in this meeting is documented by the Scrum Master and worked towards resolution outside of this meeting. No detailed discussions shall happen in this meeting.”\r\n\r\nHave you tried Agile for anything but software development, or working with interdisciplinary teams? Let us know your experience!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Agile project management as we know it', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'agile-project-management-as-we-know-it', '', '', '2015-11-28 12:43:36', '2015-11-28 12:43:36', '', '0', 'http://localhost/?p=83', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('84', '1', '2015-11-17 14:04:58', '2015-11-17 14:04:58', '', 'Agile-Development', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'agile-development', '', '', '2015-11-17 14:04:58', '2015-11-17 14:04:58', '', '83', 'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Agile-Development.png', '0', 'attachment', 'image/png', '0');
